## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Local web server (optional but recommended)

### Option 1: Simple HTTP Server

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/crabstertech/crabster-website.git
cd crabster-website

# Start a local server using Python 3
python -m http.server 8080

# Open in browser
# Navigate to: http://localhost:8080
```

### Option 2: VS Code Live Server

1. Open project in VS Code
2. Install "Live Server" extension
3. Right-click `index.html`
4. Select **"Open with Live Server"**

### Option 3: Direct File Access

Simply open `index.html` in your browser. Note: Some features may require a web server due to CORS policies.

---

## âš™ï¸ Configuration

### Review System Backend

Configure the API endpoint in `assets/js/reviews.js`:

```javascript
const API_URL = "https://crabster-backend.onrender.com/api/reviews";
```

**Required API Endpoints:**

```
GET  /api/reviews          # Fetch all reviews
POST /api/reviews          # Submit new review
```

**Review Object Schema:**

```json
{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "service": "Web Development",
  "rating": 5,
  "message": "Excellent service!",
  "date": "2025-11-24",
  "verified": true
}
```

### Contact Form

The contact form uses FormSubmit. Update the action URL in `components/contact.html`:

```html
<form action="https://formsubmit.co/your-email@example.com" method="POST">
```

**Alternative backends:**
- Formspree
- Netlify Forms
- Custom API endpoint

### Environment Variables

For production deployment, create a `.env` file:

```env
API_URL=https://your-api.com/reviews
CONTACT_EMAIL=info@crabstertech.com
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

